
msgid "Tarantool 2.10.8"
msgstr ""

msgid "Released on 2023-09-14."
msgstr ""

msgid "Release: :tarantool-release:`2.10.8`."
msgstr ""

msgid "Tag: ``2.10.8``."
msgstr ""

msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"2.10.8 is the ninth :doc:`stable </release/policy/>` version of the 2.10 "
"release series. It introduces 5 improvements and resolves 28 bugs since "
"2.10.7."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The “stable” label means that we have all planned features implemented and "
"we see no high-impact issues. However, if you encounter an issue, feel free "
"to `report it <https://github.com/tarantool/tarantool/issues>`__ on GitHub."
msgstr ""

msgid "Compatibility"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Tarantool 2.x is backward compatible with Tarantool 1.10.x in the binary "
"data layout, client-server protocol, and replication protocol."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Please :doc:`upgrade </book/admin/upgrades>` using the "
"``box.schema.upgrade()`` procedure to unlock all the new features of the 2.x"
" series."
msgstr ""

msgid "Functionality added or changed"
msgstr ""

msgid "Box"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The maximum length of ``box.cfg{}`` string parameters is now 512 instead of "
"256."
msgstr ""

msgid "Test"
msgstr ""

msgid "Fuzz"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"LuaJIT now can be fuzzed using grammar-based fuzzer (:tarantool-"
"issue:`4823`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Build"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Hardening against memory corruption attacks is now enabled by default on "
"FreeBSD (:tarantool-issue:`7536`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Added the CMake option ``FIBER_STACK_SIZE`` to set the default fiber stack "
"size."
msgstr ""

msgid "Updated libcurl to version 8.3.0."
msgstr ""

msgid "Bugs fixed"
msgstr ""

msgid "Core"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug when Tarantool failed to decode a request containing an unknown "
"IPROTO key. The bug resulted in broken connectivity between Tarantool 2.10 "
"and 2.11 (:tarantool-issue:`8745`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug causing the ``ER_CURSOR_NO_TRANSACTION`` failure for "
"transactions on synchronous spaces when the ``on_commit/on_rollback`` "
"triggers are set (:tarantool-issue:`8505`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug causing the effective session and user are not propagated to "
"``box.on_commit`` and ``box.on_rollback`` trigger callbacks when transaction"
" is synchronous (:tarantool-issue:`8742`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a crash that could happen when Tarantool is started in the "
":ref:`background mode <cfg_basic-background>` (:tarantool-issue:`6128`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug when MVCC sometimes lost gap record (:tarantool-issue:`8326`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug when MVCC rollback of prepared statement could break internal "
"invariants (:tarantool-issue:`8648`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Now MVCC engine automatically aborts a transaction if it reads changes of a "
"prepared transaction and this transaction is aborted (:tarantool-"
"issue:`8654`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug that caused writing incorrect values into the ``stream_id`` "
"field of xlog headers (:tarantool-issue:`8783`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug when a space that is referenced by a foreign key could not be "
"truncated even if the referring space was empty (:tarantool-issue:`8946`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a crash that could happen when Tarantool is compiled by ``clang`` "
"version 15 and above with enabled AddressSanitizer (`tarantool/tarantool-"
"qa#321 <https://github.com/tarantool/tarantool-qa/issues/321>`_)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a use-after-free bug in iproto server code (:tarantool-issue:`9037`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a heap-buffer-overflow bug in fiber creation code (:tarantool-"
"issue:`9026`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Memtx"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a heap-use-after-free bug in the transaction manager, which could "
"occur when performing a DDL operation concurrently with a transaction on the"
" same space (:tarantool-issue:`8781`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Vinyl"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a heap-use-after-free bug in the Vinyl read iterator caused by a race "
"between a disk read and a memory dump task. The bug could lead to a crash or"
" an invalid query result (:tarantool-issue:`8852`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Replication"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a possible failure to promote the desired node by "
"``box.ctl.promote()`` on a cluster with nodes configured with "
"``election_mode = \"candidate\"`` (:tarantool-issue:`8497`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed nodes configured with ``election_mode = 'candidate'`` spuriously "
"detecting a split-vote when another candidate should win with exactly a "
"quorum of votes for it (:tarantool-issue:`8698`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "LuaJIT"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Backported patches from the vanilla LuaJIT trunk (:tarantool-issue:`8516`, "
":tarantool-issue:`8825`). The following issues were fixed as part of this "
"activity:"
msgstr ""

msgid "Fixed canonicalization of +-0.0 keys for ``IR_NEWREF``."
msgstr ""

msgid "Fixed result truncation for ``bit.rol`` on x86_64 platforms."
msgstr ""

msgid "Fixed ``lua_yield()`` invocation inside C hooks."
msgstr ""

msgid "Fixed memory chunk allocation beyond the memory limit."
msgstr ""

msgid "Fixed TNEW load forwarding with instable types."
msgstr ""

msgid "Fixed use-def analysis for ``BC_VARG``, ``BC_FUNCV``."
msgstr ""

msgid "Fixed ``BC_UCLO`` insertion for returns."
msgstr ""

msgid "Fixed recording of ``BC_VARG`` with unused vararg values."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Initialization instructions on trace are now emitted only for the first "
"member of a union."
msgstr ""

msgid "Prevent integer overflow while parsing long strings."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed various ``^`` operator and ``math.pow()`` function inconsistencies."
msgstr ""

msgid "Fixed parsing with predicting ``next()`` and ``pairs()``."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed binary number literal parsing. Parsing of binary number with a zero "
"fractional part raises error too now."
msgstr ""

msgid "Fixed load forwarding optimization applied after table rehashing."
msgstr ""

msgid "Fixed recording of the ``BC_TSETM``."
msgstr ""

msgid "Lua"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed the xlog reader Lua module to show unknown row header fields. Before "
"this change the xlog reader silently skipped them."
msgstr ""

msgid "Netbox"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a heap-use-after-free bug in the function creating a tuple format Lua "
"object for ``net.box`` (:tarantool-issue:`8889`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed the memory leaks caused by the multi-statement transaction errors in "
"the space index building and the space format checking operations "
"(:tarantool-issue:`8773`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug in the box console implementation because of which the "
"``language`` parameter was shared between connected clients (:tarantool-"
"issue:`8817`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed an invalid memory access in a corner case of a specialized comparison "
"function (:tarantool-issue:`8899`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Console"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed console ignoring ``-i`` flag in case stdin is not a tty (:tarantool-"
"issue:`5064`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Datetime"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug raising a false positive error when creating new intervals with "
"range boundary values (:tarantool-issue:`8878`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug with buffer overflow in ``tnt_strptime`` (:tarantool-"
"issue:`8502`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Http"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a streaming connection stuck if etcd is stopped unexpectedly "
"(:tarantool-issue:`9086`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Msgpack"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed decoding datetime intervals with fields larger than possible int32 "
"values (:tarantool-issue:`8887`)."
msgstr ""
